####same code as before to compute TriCat_n^{BPR}(q,r,1) according to BPR Dyck path formula
#just with added implementation to expand into elementary symmetric polynomials 
#disclaimer: method to expand into elementary symmetric polynomials was suggested by Claude. I did test though that it seems to get me the right thing for n = 3
#only annoying thing is now all my polynomials are functions in four variables. just plug in e_1 = e_2 = 0 to get back expansion in q,t
n = 3
P = posets.TamariLattice(n)
R.<q,t,e1,e2> = PolynomialRing(QQ)
I = R.ideal([e1 - (q+t), e2 - q*t])
Groeb = I.groebner_basis()
G = P.hasse_diagram()



